# ============================================================================
# WebRTC Direct Test Environment
# ============================================================================
#
# This file is used by scripts/test_webrtc_direct.sh for isolated testing
# of the go2_ros2_sdk in WebRTC mode without DIMOS.
#
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Robot Configuration - UPDATE THESE!
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Robot WiFi IP address (check in Unitree app: Settings → Network)
# This is NOT the Ethernet IP! Robot has different IPs for WiFi vs Ethernet.
ROBOT_IP=192.168.1.103

# Connection type - MUST be webrtc for this test
CONN_TYPE=webrtc

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ROS2 Configuration
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ROS Domain ID (keep at 0 unless you have conflicts)
ROS_DOMAIN_ID=0

# ROS2 Middleware (CycloneDDS recommended for performance)
RMW_IMPLEMENTATION=rmw_cyclonedds_cpp

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: Robot Token (if your robot requires authentication)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Robot authentication token (usually not needed for local network)
# ROBOT_TOKEN=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Quick Start:
#   1. Update ROBOT_IP with your robot's WiFi IP address
#   2. Ensure robot is connected to WiFi (not just Ethernet!)
#   3. Run: ./scripts/test_webrtc_direct.sh
#
# Find Robot WiFi IP:
#   - Method 1: Unitree app → Settings → Network Settings → WiFi IP
#   - Method 2: Connect phone to robot's hotspot, check app
#   - Method 3: Router's DHCP leases page (look for "Unitree")
#
# Common WiFi IP ranges:
#   - Home networks: 192.168.1.x or 192.168.0.x
#   - Robot hotspot: 192.168.12.x
#
# Ethernet IP (for reference, DON'T use for WebRTC):
#   - Usually: 192.168.123.161 or 192.168.10.167
#
# ============================================================================
